A successful sneak is always effective.  VI has said that nothing (at all) is immune to Sneak.  Apparently, I should be able to stand behind Cazic and dance a jig - so long as he never turns and I can get in and out without ever entering his forward arc.  I *have* stood next to SeeInvis mobs and not been spotted so there's no problems there with Sneak.<br>
<br>
Hide is another story.  Level difference (and mastery of Hide skill) is said to have an effect on mobs seeing through Hide.  I'll support the theory since I know I've gotten successful Hide messages and still been spotted (very rarely) by reds.  As I've gotten up in levels, I can't remember the last time it's happened.  Nowadays, either they SeeInvis or they don't. <p><A 
